Build bullseye-gnome sdcard for raspberrypi4b:

Input files: ../uboot/out/boot.img  bootusb.img
             ../rootfs-bullseye/linaro-rootfs.img

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh   ( sudo ./mkusbimg.sh for USB2-SATA-SSD )
Eject sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to rpi4b.

Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli build-essential libjpeg-dev libpng-dev libpng16-16 pkg-config libx11-dev python3-pip python3-setuptools chromium chromium-sandbox ffmpeg mpv git pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure

git clone https://github.com/glmark2/glmark2.git -b 2021.02
cd glmark2
./waf configure --with-flavors=x11-glesv2   ( wayland-glesv2 )
./waf
sudo ./waf install

glmark2-es2-wayland  ( for wayland )
glmark2-es2          ( for x11 )

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 0 as default )

Chromium -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4
mpv swan.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
